verbose_text: Working with the same in vitro model (transformed retinal ganglion cells-RGC-5 cells), Majid (one of the researchers of the two previous studies) and colleagues showed a dose dependent increase in cell viability (0%, 18%, and 28% with, respectively, 10, 50, and 100 muM sulbutiamine), less apoptosis, less caspase-3 activity, and a decrease in ROS levels for the 100 muM dose.
